1. Load data, preprocess¶

Now we load expression and meta data.

In [2]:
lognorm_expr = pd.read_csv('rpca_lognorm.csv', index_col = 0)
meta = pd.read_csv('rpca_meta.csv', index_col = 0)

Since in this example, we load log normalized data from Seurat, so we only need to perform scale preprocessing. In this case, we use only highly variable genes for integration. One can also load all genes as the input.

In [3]:
adata_prep = ad.AnnData(np.array(lognorm_expr).T, dtype=np.float32)
adata_prep.var_names = lognorm_expr.index.values
adata_prep.obs = meta
sc.pp.scale(adata_prep)
adata_prep.layers['scale'] = adata_prep.X
adata_prep

2. Estimate cell states¶

Load estimated cell states. In our example, we aim to recover signal for seurat-integrated data. Therefore, we use Seurat-integrated PCA embedding as cell states.

In [5]:
pcs = pd.read_csv('rpca_pcs.csv', index_col = 0)
#loadings = pd.read_csv('rpca_loadings.csv', index_col = 0)
#print(pcs.shape, loadings.shape)
In [6]:
Z_corr_combined = pcs.loc[adata_prep.obs_names]
print( np.all(Z_corr_combined.index == adata_prep.obs_names) )
adata_prep.obsm['Cmat'] = Z_corr_combined.to_numpy()

Mmat = cnova.model.fit_M(adata_prep, integrate_key = integrate_key)
adata_prep.varm['Mmat'] = Mmat.T
adata_prep.layers['main_effect'] = adata_prep.obsm['Cmat'] @ adata_prep.varm['Mmat'].T

integrated = ad.AnnData(adata_prep.layers['denoised'], dtype=np.float32)
integrated.obs = adata_prep.obs.copy()
integrated.var_names = adata_prep.var_names
sc.pp.neighbors(integrated, n_neighbors=15, n_pcs=30)
sc.tl.umap(integrated)
